  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Qpop is a customer-facing application designed to enhance interaction and engagement at the point of sale through a dedicated touchscreen interface. Always facing the customer, Qpop allows for seamless interaction during the sales process by:</p><ul><li><p>Displaying in-store advertisements and promotions</p></li><li><p>Showing real-time ticket details for customer review</p></li><li><p>Presenting electronic forms and waivers for acknowledgment</p></li><li><p>Capturing electronic signatures for payments via integrated devices</p></li></ul><p>An Android tablet works well as a kiosk device, allowing you to restrict it to a single app for your business. The <strong>Kiosk Browser Lockdown</strong> app can help keep the focus on the Qpop Companion app by preventing navigation to other apps or pages.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: This app is not required to use QP Companion, and we do not own or manage Kiosk Browser Lockdown. Please use it at your discretion.</p><h3 id=\"Qpop\u2122Companion-EnableKioskModeonAndroid-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936588867/Qpop+Companion+-+Enable+Kiosk+Mode+on+iOS\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936588867\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion - Enable Kiosk Mode on iOS</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937047567/Qpop+Companion+Resources+with+Video\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937047567\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936654410/Qpop+Companion+Troubleshooting\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936654410\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Troubleshooting</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172717.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Qpop\u2122Companion-EnableKioskModeonAndroid-DownloadtheKioskBrowserLockdownApplication\">Download the Kiosk Browser Lockdown Application</h2><p>On your tablet, navigate to the Google Play store and search for Kiosk Browser Lockdown. Install the application. Open the application and follow the instructions to \u2018always select Kiosk Browser as your Home Page.\u2019</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172727.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172732.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Kiosk Browser, tap <strong>Options</strong> and then tap <strong>Settings</strong>. Enter the default password: 0000 then tap <strong>OK</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172738.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"594\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172743.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172749.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Settings page, tap <strong>Admin </strong>and change the password to a memorable, secure password. Save and go back to Settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172754.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the settings page, go to <strong>General</strong> \u2192 <strong>Kiosk URL</strong>. Enter the URL for your database. Save your changes and exit the settings page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172758.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>When you exit Settings, you will be routed to your new launch screen, where you can log in and <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://repairq.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/115005371628\" rel=\"nofollow\">pair your Qpop Companion</a>.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: If you choose to keep the tablet in always-on status, make sure your device is plugged into a power source.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936523314/image-20230608-172804.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
